## 2026-03-28 - Token impact summary on edit
- Enhanced `scanTokenUsage` in heatmapScanning.ts to walk each found layer's parent chain and extract the nearest COMPONENT/COMPONENT_SET/INSTANCE ancestor name as `componentName`. The response now includes `componentNames: string[]` (unique component names across all matching layers).
- Rewrote `TokenDependents.tsx` to show: (1) impact summary banner "N layers across M components" with a "Highlight" button that sends `highlight-layer-by-token`; (2) clickable component count that toggles a pill-list of component names; (3) before/after value diff in the banner for non-color types (was only colors before); (4) component name shown as a second line under each layer name in the layers list.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/plugin/heatmapScanning.ts` ~L211 (new `findComponentAncestor`, updated `scanTokenUsage`), `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/TokenDependents.tsx` (full rewrite with new BoundLayer.componentName field and impact summary UI)

